(secondQuint)Connected Catheter Clinical Feasibility Study.

 The Connected Catheter is a replaceable urinary prosthesis that is intended for use in male patients 18 years of age or older who have impaired bladder emptying due to neurogenic lower urinary tract dysfunction, and who are capable of operating the device in accordance with the provided instructions for use, or who have trained caregivers capable of doing the same.

 The device must be replaced every 29 days (or less).

